<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Ayurveda - Eternal Science of Life</title>
  <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com"></script>
</head>
<body class="bg-gradient-to-b from-green-50 to-white text-gray-800 font-serif">

  <!-- Header -->
  <header class="bg-green-600 text-white text-center py-8 shadow-md">
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold">🌿 Ayurveda: The Eternal Science of Life</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 italic text-lg">“Hita hitaṃ sukhaṃ duḥkham āyustasya hitaḥ hitaṃ | mānām ca taccha yuktaṃ āyurvedaḥ sa ucyate ||”<br>– Charaka Samhita</p>
  </header>

  <main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10 space-y-16">

    <!-- Introduction -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl text-green-700 font-semibold mb-4">What is Ayurveda?</h2>
      <p class="text-lg">
        Ayurveda, literally meaning "the Science of Life" in Sanskrit, is an ancient Indian system of medicine and natural healing that has been practiced for over 5,000 years. It combines physical, psychological, and spiritual well-being through lifestyle alignment, dietary discipline, and nature-based healing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Quotes and Wisdom -->
    <section class="bg-green-100 p-6 rounded-xl shadow">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-4">📜 Ancient Wisdom</h2>
      <blockquote class="italic text-lg text-gray-700 border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4 mb-4">
        “Shariram adyam khalu dharmasadhanam.” <br>– “The body is indeed the foremost instrument of dharma.” – Charaka
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote class="italic text-lg text-gray-700 border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-4">
        “Loka Purusha Samya Siddhanta” – “The microcosm (human) reflects the macrocosm (universe).”
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <!-- Tridosha Guide -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl text-green-700 font-semibold mb-4">The Tridoshas: Vata, Pitta, Kapha</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-indigo-700">🌬️ Vata (Air + Ether)</h3>
          <p>Controls movement, nervous system, creativity. Imbalance causes anxiety, dryness, bloating.</p>
          <p class="mt-2"><strong>Balance with:</strong> warmth, oil massage, grounding food, routine.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-600">🔥 Pitta (Fire + Water)</h3>
          <p>Governs digestion, metabolism, intellect. Imbalance causes anger, inflammation, ulcers.</p>
          <p class="mt-2"><strong>Balance with:</strong> cooling foods, calm mind, avoid spicy or acidic food.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white border border-green-200 p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-700">🌊 Kapha (Water + Earth)</h3>
          <p>Responsible for structure, lubrication, stability. Imbalance causes lethargy, congestion, weight gain.</p>
          <p class="mt-2"><strong>Balance with:</strong> activity, warm spices, light dry food, variety.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Panchakarma & Therapies -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl text-green-700 font-semibold mb-4">🌿 Panchakarma & Ayurvedic Therapies</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Panchakarma is Ayurveda’s unique purification and rejuvenation treatment. It includes:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2 text-lg">
        <li><strong>Vamana:</strong> Therapeutic vomiting to eliminate toxins</li>
        <li><strong>Virechana:</strong> Purgation therapy for liver & intestine</li>
        <li><strong>Basti:</strong> Medicinal enema for colon cleansing</li>
        <li><strong>Nasya:</strong> Nasal therapy to clear head and sinuses</li>
        <li><strong>Raktamokshana:</strong> Bloodletting to cleanse the blood</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Daily Routine -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl text-green-700 font-semibold mb-4">☀️ Dinacharya – Ideal Daily Routine</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-lg">
        <div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Wake before sunrise (Brahma Muhurta)</li>
            <li>Oil pulling (Gandusha)</li>
            <li>Nasya (nose oiling)</li>
            <li>Abhyanga (self-massage)</li>
            <li>Yoga & Meditation</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2">
            <li>Light, warm breakfast</li>
            <li>Eat largest meal at noon</li>
            <li>Walk after meals</li>
            <li>Early dinner, no late-night work</li>
            <li>Sleep by 10 PM</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Ayurvedic Diet -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl text-green-700 font-semibold mb-4">🍽️ Ayurvedic Diet: Eating for Balance</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Ayurveda recommends a seasonal, dosha-aligned diet. Food should be fresh, cooked, and full of Prana (life force).</p>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white shadow p-4 rounded-lg border border-green-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">6 Tastes (Shad Rasa)</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1">
            <li>Sweet – grounding, nourishing</li>
            <li>Sour – stimulating digestion</li>
            <li>Salty – water balance</li>
            <li>Pungent – metabolism booster</li>
            <li>Bitter – detoxifying</li>
            <li>Astringent – tightening and cooling</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white shadow p-4 rounded-lg border border-green-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2">Avoid Incompatible Foods (Viruddha Ahara)</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-1">
            <li>Milk + fruit</li>
            <li>Fish + dairy</li>
            <li>Yogurt + night time</li>
            <li>Heating honey</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Rejuvenation & Rasayana -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl text-green-700 font-semibold mb-4">💎 Rasayana – Rejuvenation Therapy</h2>
      <p class="text-lg">
        Rasayana aims to revitalize the body, strengthen immunity (Ojas), and slow aging. Famous Rasayanas include:
      </p>
      <ul class="list-disc ml-6 space-y-2 text-lg">
        <li><strong>Chyawanprash:</strong> Immune booster</li>
        <li><strong>Ashwagandha:</strong> Stress relief & vitality</li>
        <li><strong>Brahmi:</strong> Memory and intellect enhancer</li>
        <li><strong>Shilajit:</strong> Mineral-rich longevity supplement</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Modern Applications -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl text-green-700 font-semibold mb-4">🧘‍♂️ Ayurveda in the Modern World</h2>
      <p class="text-lg">
        From herbal teas to yoga retreats, Ayurvedic principles are integrated globally. Holistic wellness centers, medical schools,
        and integrative medicine clinics are embracing Ayurvedic wisdom alongside modern science.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Conclusion -->
    <section>
      <h2 class="text-3xl text-green-700 font-semibold mb-4">🌟 Conclusion: A Way of Life</h2>
      <p class="text-lg">
        Ayurveda is not just a medical system—it's a sacred art of living consciously. It guides us to live in harmony with nature,
        understand our inner constitution, and empower healing from within. In every breath and bite, Ayurveda encourages us to
        choose balance, mindfulness, and joy.
      </p>
    </section>

  </main>


</body>
</html>
